Chocolate Cake and Chocolate Icing
via???

CAKE INGREDIENTS:
* 1 1/4 cup flour
* 8 tbls (1/4 cup?) unsweetened cocoa
* 2 tsp baking powder
* 1 tsp cinnamon
* 1 cup sugar
* 1 tsp vanilla extract
* 1/2 cup milk
* 1/2 cup vegetable (or peanut) oil
* 2 eggs

CAKE DIRECTIONS:


1.  Preheat oven to 350F/180C
2.  Grease 9-10in cake tin
3.  In a large bowl mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar in a bowl
4.  In a separate bowl beat together milk, oil, eggs, and vanilla
5.  Beat wet mixture into dry mixture portions at a time on slow setting until combined
6.  Pour mixture into your cake tin, pop into oven for 35-45 minutes
7.  Let cool for 10-20, then turn over onto wire rack for cooling for 10-20
8.  Refrigerate for at least 2 hours
9.  Slice cake through middle horizontally making to layers
10.  Refrigerate while making the frosting - cake directions to continue....

----------

ICING INGREDIENTS:

* 2/3 cup heavy cream
* 9 oz / 260 g semi-sweet chocolate (40-50% cocoa) finely chopped

ICING DIRECTIONS:

1.  Heat cream in a sauce pan on low-med heat until hot but not boiling
2.  Remove from heat, stir in chocolate, portions at a time until combined and smooth
3.  Let cool 10-20 minutes then refrigerate for 1 hour
4.  Split icing into 3rds

----------

CONT'D CAKE DIRECTIONS:

11.  Take icing and cake layers out of the refrigerator
12.  Using a rubber spatula apply 1/3 of icing mixture to the middle layer of the cake
13.  Apply 1/3 icing mixture to the top of the cake
14.  Apply the remaining icing mixture to the sides of the cake
15.  Let set for an hour in the refrigerator, serve at room temperature
